---- MODULE nbacc_ray97 ----
plus    //TLC Configuration : CONSTANT N =2 INVARIANT TypeOK SPECIFICATION Spec    /* Comments */     PROGRAM counters             * Messages which are received      ** Processes, including the crashed ones       RECEIVE new messages          The failure detector sends a nondeterministically  NEW prediction to process self.   Proc Self becomes Crash.. Sends YES message    NO Message is sent by procSelf and thinks that some other processes have not committed yet . All Processes vote Yes, Some others Vote No      Add the weak fainstre condition     NonTriv == ( /\ A i in NProcs: pc[i] = "YEs"  \/\ [](\A self In Proc :(fd [self ]= FALSE)) => <> (\a Self IN PROC:(pc [_Self_ CRASH]))   Sends a NO message    /* End of Comments */
This TLA+ program is designed to simulate the behavior and failure detection in distributed systems. It uses process counters, messages received by processes (NBAC), failures detectors reporting whether some other processing has crashed or not all including self-crash scenario etc., as per given rules/conventions above with comments explaining each step performed during execution of TLA+ program:
